 across Canada, with approximately 100 from the United States, Britain, or Europe. In compiling a catalogue of these exhibitions, Evelyn McMann has produced a comprehensive record of Canadian art during nine decades of tremendous development. Her work refers the reader to biographical information about the majority of the artists, and makes available for the first time information on hundreds of lesser-known artists. The many cross-references make it possible to locate artists who exhibited under two or more names, and the record of more than 150 prizes award through the exhibitions adds another useful resource. For reasearchers and art historians this volume provides an invaluable point of access to a vast body of Canadian art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArt, CanadianvExhibitionsvIndexes. 0aArt, CanadianxExhibitionsvIndexes. 0aArt, Moderny19th centuryvExhibitionsvIndexes. 0aArt, Moderny19th centuryxExhibitionsvIndexes. 0aArt, Moderny20th centuryvExhibitionsvIndexes. 0aArt, Moderny20th centuryxExhibitionsvIndexes. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757622640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487576226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487576226.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK